Pre-Yext average was 92.8%. Percentage of searches where a piece of data from the Yext Knowledge Graph was returned. Inverse of Zero Hit Rate.

Pre-Yext this number averaged 22.7%. Yext does not count multiple clicks within a search in this metric and Samsung does therefore our metric is generally lower than Samsungs. If Yext were to calculate this metric the way Samsung does, the CTR displayed is 1-2% higher.

Pre-Yext average was 20.1%. Answers Clicks = when a user clicks on a result within that specific vertical. If majority of clicks are in the "0" position, then users are getting served the best information at the top of the results.

Answers Searches = when a user runs a query, the number of verticals returned for that search. Answers Clicks = when a user clicks on a result within that specific vertical. If majority of clicks are in the "0" position, then users are getting served the best information at the top of the results.
